@code JavaScript
/**

* @section Potential Improvements
  */

/**

* @subsection Improvement 1 - Add Input Validation
*
* Current implementation:
*
* ```js
  ```
* localTask.tags
* ```
  ```
*
* Safer alternative:
*
* ```js
  ```
* const localTags = localTask.tags || [];
* ```
  ```

*/

/**

* @subsection Improvement 2 - Replace Tuple Return Values
*
* Current:
*
* ```js
  ```
* return [mergedTask, shouldUpdateLocal, shouldUpdateRemote];
* ```
  ```
*
* More readable:
*
* ```js
  ```
* return {
* mergedTask,
* shouldUpdateLocal,
* shouldUpdateRemote
* };
* ```
  ```

*/

/**

* @subsection Improvement 3 - Centralize Merge Rules
*
* Merge policy is currently embedded directly in conditionals.
*
* Could extract reusable helpers:
*
* ```js
  ```
* mergeField(fieldName)
* ```
  ```

*/

/**

* @subsection Improvement 4 - Reduce Repeated Flag Assignments
*
* Repeated patterns:
*
* ```js
  ```
* shouldUpdateLocal = true;
* ```
  ```
*
* could be simplified with helper utilities.
  */

/**

* @subsection Improvement 5 - Defensive Date Handling
*
* Safer parsing:
*
* ```js
  ```
* const localDate = Date.parse(localTask.updatedAt);
* ```
  ```
*
* combined with validation checks.
  */

/**

* @subsection Improvement 6 - Preserve Immutable Merge Semantics
*
* Current implementation uses shallow copies:
*
* ```js
  ```
* {...localTask}
* ```
  ```
*
* Nested objects may still share references.
  */

/**

* @subsection Improvement 7 - Clarify Merge Policy Documentation
*
* The algorithm combines multiple merge strategies:
*
* | Field Type | Merge Strategy |
* |---|---|
* | Standard fields | Last-write-wins |
* | Completion status | DONE always wins |
* | Tags | Union merge |
*
* Explicit documentation would improve maintainability.
  */
@end

